    "eyebrow": "Orientation",
    "num": "01",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">01</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Orientation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Welcome: Exploring the Term 'Texican'</h2><ul><li>Introduction to the lesson focus: the term 'Texican'</li><li>Understanding contested terminology in Texas history</li><li>Preview of key terms: Texican, Texian, Texan</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This lesson begins by orienting learners to the term 'Texican', a historically rich and contested label. We will clarify how it differs from related terms and why understanding these distinctions matters for Texas history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Consider how the term 'Texican' might reflect cultural identity differently than 'Texian' or 'Texan' depending on historical context.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Reflect on what you think 'Texican' means before we explore historical definitions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming 'Texican' is just a misspelling or synonym of 'Texan' without historical nuance.</p></div></div>",
