    "num": "06",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Concepts</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Historical Context: Texas under Mexican Rule</h2><ul><li>Texas was part of Mexico until 1836</li><li>Mexican government encouraged settlement by Anglo empresarios</li><li>Texicans were established Mexican residents with cultural ties to Mexico</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Understanding Texas as Mexican territory explains the origins of Texican identity and the arrival of Anglo settlers called Texians. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Stephen F. Austin received a land grant from Mexico to settle Anglo families in Texas, creating a Texian community among Texicans.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain how Mexican policies shaped the demographic and cultural landscape of early Texas.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring Mexican sovereignty and its impact on early Texas settlement.</p></div></div>",
