    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Concepts</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Settlement Patterns of Texicans</h2><ul><li>Texicans settled primarily in established towns and ranches</li><li>Often held land through Mexican land grants</li><li>Coexisted with Anglo settlements but maintained distinct communities</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlement reflected continuity of Mexican landholding traditions and adaptation to new Anglo presence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> San Antonio was a major Texican settlement with deep Mexican roots, contrasting with newer Anglo colonies.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify differences in settlement patterns between Texicans and Anglo settlers.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming all early Texas settlers lived in similar types of communities.</p></div></div>",
