      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> Texican settlement reflected continuity of Mexican landholding traditions and adaptation to new Anglo presence.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from lauriemooremoore.com; everything-everywhere.com. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Texicans settled primarily in established towns and ranches</li><li>Often held land through Mexican land grants</li><li>Coexisted with Anglo settlements but maintained distinct communities</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>San Antonio was a major Texican settlement with deep Mexican roots, contrasting with newer Anglo colonies.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Identify differences in settlement patterns between Texicans and Anglo settlers.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Assuming all early Texas settlers lived in similar types of communities.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> lauriemooremoore.com; everything-everywhere.com <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p>"
