    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">10</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Practice: Classify Historical Figures</h2><ul><li>Given brief biographies, identify if the person was Texican, Texian, or Texan</li><li>Consider cultural background, time period, and political allegiance</li><li>Discuss reasoning with peers or reflect individually</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Applying terminology to real historical figures helps solidify understanding of distinctions and contexts. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Stephen F. Austin: Anglo settler under Mexican rule → Texian</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Classify: José Antonio Navarro, Sam Houston, Juan Seguín, William B. Travis</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Relying solely on name or ethnicity without considering historical context.</p></div></div>",
