    "num": "16",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">16</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Patterns</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Mexican Land Grant Policies and Empresarios</h2><ul><li>Mexico used land grants to encourage settlement in Texas</li><li>Empresarios like Stephen F. Austin facilitated Anglo-American colonization</li><li>Land grants shaped settlement distribution and community development</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mexican authorities issued land grants to empresarios who recruited settlers, mainly Anglo-Americans, to populate Texas. This policy influenced settlement patterns and the cultural landscape of Texican communities. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Stephen F. Austin received a grant to settle 300 families, creating a cluster of Anglo settlements within Mexican Texas.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Examine how land grant policies can influence demographic and cultural changes in a region.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming land grants were evenly distributed or solely Mexican ignores the role of empresarios and Anglo settlers.</p></div></div>",
