    "num": "19",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Lifestyle</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Economic Activities and Lifestyle</h2><ul><li>Agriculture and ranching were primary economic pursuits</li><li>Settlements were often self-sufficient with local trade</li><li>Cultural practices influenced daily life and community structure</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlers engaged mainly in farming and cattle ranching, supporting self-sufficient communities with local markets. Their lifestyle reflected a blend of Mexican and Anglo-American customs. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican rancher might raise cattle using Mexican vaquero techniques while adopting Anglo-American property management.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify how economic activities reflect cultural influences in frontier communities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming economic practices were uniform ignores the hybrid nature of Texican livelihoods.</p></div></div>",
