    "id": "slide21",
    "eyebrow": "Settlement Analysis",
    "num": "21",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">21</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Map Analysis: Understanding Texican Settlement Patterns</h2><ul><li>Examine settlement locations relative to rivers and resources</li><li>Identify clusters of Anglo-American and Mexican communities</li><li>Consider geographic factors influencing settlement success</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Analyzing settlement maps reveals how geography, land grants, and cultural factors shaped Texican community distribution and interactions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Mapping Austin’s colony shows concentration along the Brazos River, highlighting strategic settlement choices.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Use provided maps to identify patterns and infer reasons for settlement locations.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking geographic context can lead to misinterpretation of settlement dynamics.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide21\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39; as used historically?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;An Anglo-American settler in Texas after 1836&quot;,&quot;A Mexican citizen living in Texas before independence&quot;,&quot;A person of mixed Mexican and Anglo heritage living in Texas before 1836&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe in Texas&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:2,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; historically referred to people of mixed Mexican and Anglo heritage or Mexican settlers in Texas before independence, distinguishing them from later &#39;Texians&#39; and &#39;Texans&#39;.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how Mexican land grant policies influenced the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should describe the role of Mexican land grants and empresarios like Stephen F. Austin in attracting settlers, shaping community layouts, and influencing economic activities such as ranching and farming. It should mention how these policies created a unique Texican identity blending Mexican and Anglo-American elements.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Mexican land grant policies, administered through empresarios like Stephen F. Austin, provided land to settlers which encouraged migration and settlement in Texas. These grants shaped where Texicans lived and how they organized their communities, often blending Mexican legal and cultural traditions with Anglo-American practices, influencing their ranching and farming lifestyle.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Mexican land grants encouraged settlement by giving land to settlers through empresarios&quot;,&quot;Stephen F. Austin’s colony was a key example of how land grants shaped Texican communities&quot;,&quot;Land grant policies influenced Texican lifestyle by promoting ranching and farming&quot;,&quot;The policies helped create a mixed cultural identity among Texicans&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
