    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">24</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Knowledge: Texican Identity in Historical Context</h2><ul><li>Consider how Texican cultural hybridity influenced political alliances</li><li>Analyze the impact of land grant policies on community cohesion</li><li>Evaluate the role of settlement patterns in shaping Texican responses to Mexican authority</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Applying understanding of Texican cultural and settlement dynamics helps explain their complex role in early Texas history and political conflicts. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texicans’ mixed loyalties and settlement experiences contributed to shifting support during the Texas Revolution.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief analysis of how cultural identity and land policies might affect Texican political decisions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Separating cultural identity from political behavior misses their interconnection.</p></div></div>",
