    "id": "slide26",
    "eyebrow": "Political Tensions",
    "num": "26",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">26</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Tensions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Mexican Policies and Texican Responses</h2><ul><li>Mexico imposed laws to control Texas settlement and governance</li><li>Texicans reacted with resistance and negotiation</li><li>Key laws included restrictions on immigration and customs duties</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mexico’s government enacted policies to regulate Texas, including limiting Anglo immigration and enforcing customs duties. Texicans often resisted these measures, leading to political friction that contributed to the Texas Revolution (s7, s12). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The Law of April 6, 1830, banned further US immigration, provoking Texican opposition.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Mexican laws affected Texican political actions and attitudes.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the role of Mexican law in shaping Texican resistance.</p></div></div>",
