    "id": "slide27",
    "eyebrow": "Texican Political Actions",
    "num": "27",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">27</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Political Actions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Participation in Early Texas Conventions</h2><ul><li>Texicans attended political conventions to voice concerns</li><li>They debated loyalty to Mexico versus calls for autonomy</li><li>Conventions laid groundwork for Texas Revolution</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans actively participated in political conventions such as the 1832 and 1833 Conventions, where they debated issues like immigration, governance, and relations with Mexico. These gatherings reflected their political engagement and growing desire for self-determination (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> At the 1833 Convention, Texicans drafted petitions requesting statehood separate from Coahuila.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate the significance of Texican involvement in these conventions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring Texican agency by assuming only Anglo settlers led political movements.</p></div></div>",
