    "eyebrow": "Primary Source Analysis",
    "num": "28",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Source Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Examining Texican Letters and Petitions</h2><ul><li>Primary documents reveal Texican perspectives on Mexican rule</li><li>Letters express concerns about laws and governance</li><li>Petitions show organized political action</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Analyzing Texican letters and petitions from the 1820s and 1830s provides direct insight into their political views and responses to Mexican policies. These documents show a community engaged in negotiation and resistance (s12, s13). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A petition from Texicans requested repeal of customs duties, emphasizing economic hardship.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Read a sample Texican petition and identify key political demands.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Relying solely on secondary summaries without engaging with primary texts.</p></div></div>",
