    "id": "slide29",
    "eyebrow": "Case Study",
    "num": "29",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">29</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Case Study</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Role in the Battle of Gonzales</h2><ul><li>Texicans resisted Mexican troops demanding a cannon</li><li>This event marked the first armed conflict of the Texas Revolution</li><li>Texican actions showed willingness to defend local rights</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Battle of Gonzales in 1835 involved Texicans refusing to return a cannon to Mexican forces, symbolizing their resistance to Mexican authority and sparking the Texas Revolution (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican settlers organized militias to defend the cannon, demonstrating political and military agency.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how this event reflects Texican political attitudes and actions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing the battle as solely an Anglo settler conflict without Texican involvement.</p></div></div>",
