    "id": "slide30",
    "eyebrow": "Political Conflict Dynamics",
    "num": "30",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">30</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Conflict Dynamics</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Relations with Mexican Authorities</h2><ul><li>Texicans negotiated with and sometimes opposed Mexican officials</li><li>Conflicts arose over governance, law enforcement, and cultural differences</li><li>Some Texicans sought compromise, others favored rebellion</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans’ interactions with Mexican authorities were complex, involving negotiation, resistance, and occasional cooperation. These dynamics influenced the escalation toward revolution (s2, s13). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican leaders petitioned Mexican officials for reforms while preparing militias for defense.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss how Texican strategies varied in dealing with Mexican authorities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming uniform Texican hostility toward Mexican government.</p></div></div>",
