    "id": "slide31",
    "eyebrow": "Political Conflict",
    "num": "31",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">31</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Conflict</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Involvement in the Texas Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texicans fought alongside Anglo settlers in key battles</li><li>They contributed knowledge of terrain and local politics</li><li>Their participation was crucial to revolutionary success</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">During the Texas Revolution, Texicans actively participated in military engagements, providing critical support and local expertise that aided the revolutionary cause (s7, s12). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican fighters joined the Siege of Bexar, helping to capture San Antonio.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify ways Texicans contributed to revolutionary efforts beyond combat.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Minimizing Texican contributions by focusing only on Anglo settlers.</p></div></div>",
