    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">40</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Daily Life and Economy</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Agricultural Practices and Land Use</h2><ul><li>Texicans cultivated crops like corn, beans, and cotton.</li><li>Land grants from Mexican authorities shaped farming locations.</li><li>Agriculture was supplemented by livestock ranching.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican daily life centered on farming and ranching, supported by Mexican land grant policies. Primary land records reveal patterns of settlement and economic activity. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican family farmed a land grant parcel growing staple crops and raising cattle.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a land grant document to identify agricultural potential and constraints.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the role of Mexican land policies leads to incomplete understanding of Texican settlement.</p></div></div>",
