    "num": "42",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">42</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Daily Life and Economy</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Economic Challenges and Adaptations of Texicans</h2><ul><li>Texicans faced challenges like limited markets and resource scarcity.</li><li>They adapted by diversifying crops and engaging in trade networks.</li><li>Economic resilience was key to community survival.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Economic constraints required Texicans to be resourceful, balancing subsistence farming with trade. Primary economic data show patterns of adaptation to frontier conditions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texicans traded surplus cotton for manufactured goods from nearby towns.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify economic strategies Texicans used to overcome frontier challenges.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texican economy was static ignores their adaptive strategies.</p></div></div>",
