    "eyebrow": "Daily Life and Economy",
    "num": "43",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">43</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Daily Life and Economy</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Primary Sources: Letters and Land Records</h2><ul><li>Letters provide personal insights into Texican daily life and concerns.</li><li>Land records document settlement patterns and property ownership.</li><li>Analyzing these sources reveals economic and social realities.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Primary documents like letters and land grants offer direct evidence of Texican experiences, enabling reconstruction of their lifestyle and challenges. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter from a Texican settler describes crop failures and community support.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a sample letter to identify key themes about Texican life.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking context in primary sources can lead to misinterpretation.</p></div></div>",
