    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">44</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Daily Life and Economy</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Document Analysis Activity: Reconstructing Texican Life</h2><ul><li>Examine provided letters and land grant excerpts.</li><li>Identify economic activities, social roles, and challenges.</li><li>Discuss how these documents reflect Texican community life.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Hands-on analysis of primary documents helps learners apply source evaluation skills and deepen understanding of Texican daily life. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Learners identify references to crop planting cycles and family roles in a letter.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Work in groups to analyze documents and present findings on Texican lifestyle.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Focusing only on surface details without connecting to broader context limits insight.</p></div></div>",
