    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">48</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Role Play: Negotiating Texican-Native Relations</h2><ul><li>Simulate a negotiation between Texican settlers and Native tribe leaders.</li><li>Consider economic needs, land use, and cultural perspectives.</li><li>Aim to reach a mutually beneficial agreement or understand conflict causes.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Role play helps learners embody historical perspectives, deepening empathy and understanding of complex Texican-Native interactions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s14\">[14]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> One group represents Texicans seeking land access; another represents Comanche protecting territory.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Prepare arguments and negotiate terms reflecting historical realities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying positions or ignoring cultural context reduces role play effectiveness.</p></div></div>",
