    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">56</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Group Discussion Preparation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Reconciling Conflicting Accounts of Texican History</h2><ul><li>Identify key points of disagreement among sources</li><li>Discuss possible reasons for conflicting narratives</li><li>Consider the impact of author background and context</li><li>Explore methods to synthesize differing perspectives</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Preparing for group discussion, learners analyze conflicts in sources to develop strategies for critical reconciliation and deeper understanding. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s17\">[17]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Disagreement over whether 'Texian' included Mexican-origin settlers reflects differing political and cultural interpretations.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> List two conflicting views on Texican identity and propose ways to reconcile them.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring conflicts or forcing consensus without critical analysis.</p></div></div>",
